created: 2022-10-31, last updated: 2026-04-17, [Read more](https://github.com/pocketbase/pocketbase/discussions/879)

You have to use `apis.StaticDirectoryHandler`, not `echo.StaticDirectoryHandler` because of a conflict with the `RemoveTrailingSlashMiddleware`.
Additioanlly, PocketBase v0.8.0-rc1 comes with new `StaticDirectoryHandler` where you can allow index.html forwarding on missing files by changing the last argument to `true`:
```
package main
import (
"log"
"os"
...
)
func main() {
app := pocketbase.New()
app.OnBeforeServe().Add(func(e *core.ServeEvent) error {
// serves static files from the provided public dir (if exists)
e.Router.GET("/*", apis.StaticDirectoryHandler(os.DirFS("public"), true))
return nil
})
if err := app.Start(); err != nil {
log.Fatal(err)
}
}
```
...
I don't plan making changes to this part of the code, so you can give it a try by updating the dependency in your `go.mod` file to:
```
github.com/pocketbase/pocketbase v0.8.0-rc1
```
And then run `go get` (or `go mod tidy`).

